<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-06T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="740" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-06T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1916, 7 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3006. Your 3896 of March 1. Again unofficially request Foreign Office
                                to grant cyanide permit which has already been paid for and
                                therefore involves no transfer of money to Germany. Appeals are
                                being received from textile manufacturers in all sections of the
                                country for bleaching materials made from cyanide in which Roessler
                                and Hasslacher have monopoly. The matter is very urgent and refusal
                                would have serious consequences. Reply immediately.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>